a Italia]]\n* '''{{flag|Jamaica}}''': [[Jamaica Labour Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Japan}}''': [[Liberal Democratic Party (Japan)|Liberal Democratic Party]]<ref>{{Citation |first=Pradyumna P. |last=Karan |title=Japan in the 21st century: environment, economy, and society |publisher=University Press of Kentucky |year=2005 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wS5kcRvShg8C&pg=PT259|isbn=978-0813137773 }}</ref><ref name=\"Hoover2011\">{{cite book|editor=William D. Hoover|title=Historical Dictionary of Postwar Japan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Exa7XoW-1n8C&pg=PA211|year=2011|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7539-5|page=211}}</ref>\n*'''{{flag|Kosovo}}''': [[Democratic League of Kosovo]], [[Alliance for the Future of Kosovo]]\n* '''{{flag|Latvia}}''': [[Unity (Latvian political party)|Unity]]\n* '''{{flag|Lebanon}}''': [[National Bloc (Lebanon)|National Bloc]]\n* '''{{flag|Lithuania}}''': [[Homeland Union]]<ref name=\"Bugajski2002B\">{{cite book|author=Janusz Bugajski|title=Political Parties of Eastern Europe: A Guide to Politics in the Post-Communist Era|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9gGKtLTQlUcC&pg=PA141|year=2002|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-1-56324-676-0|page=141}}</ref>\n* '''{{flag|Malta}}''': [[Nationalist Party (Malta)|Nationalist Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Moldova}}''': [[Liberal Democratic Party of Moldova]]\n* '''{{flag|Montenegro}}''': [[Movement for Changes]]<ref name=\"Bakke2010\"/>\n* '''{{flag|Morocco}}''': [[Constitutional Union (Morocco)|Constitutional Union]]<ref>{{Citation|author1=Abdo Baaklini|author2=Guilain Denoeux|first3=Robert|last3=Springborg|title=Legislative Politics in the Arab World: The Resurgence of Democratic Institutions|publisher=Lynne Riener|year=1999|page=129}}</ref>\n* '''{{flag|Netherlands}}''': [[Christian Democratic Appeal]], [[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy]]<ref name=\"Timmermans2014\">{{cite book|author1=Arco Timmermans |author2=Edwin van Rooyen |author3=Gerrit Voerman |chapter=Policy analysis and pol