litical party)|Agreement]]\n* '''{{flag|Portugal}}''': [[Social Democratic Party (Portugal)|Social Democratic Party]]<ref name=\"Krouwel2012\">{{cite book|author=Andr\u00e9 Krouwel|title=Party Transformations in European Democracies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w4DMRL66gOIC&pg=PA348|year=2012|publisher=SUNY Press|isbn=978-1-4384-4483-3|page=348}}</ref>\n* '''{{flag|Romania}}''': [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Russia}}''': [[Civic Platform (Russia)|Civic Platform]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/russia.html|title= 2016 Russia legislative elections: State Duma|publisher=Parties and Elections in Europe|date=2016|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n* '''{{flag|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines}}''': [[New Democratic Party (Saint Vincent and the Grenadines)|New Democratic Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Serbia}}''': [[People's Party (Serbia, 2017)|People's Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Singapore}}''': [[People's Action Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Slovakia}}''': [[Ordinary People (Slovakia)|Ordinary People]], [[Most\u2013H\u00edd]],<ref>{{Citation |first=Jozef |last=St\u00edskala |title=Party System of Slovak Republic and its Stability after 2010 and 2012 Elections in Comparative Perspective |journal=Slovak Journal of Political Sciences |volume=12 |year=2012 |number=3 |page=233}}</ref> [[Civic Conservative Party (Slovak party)|Civic Conservative Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Slovenia}}''': [[Slovenian Democratic Party]]<ref name=\"Cerami2006\">{{cite book|author=Alfio Cerami|title=Social Policy in Central and Eastern Europe: The Emergence of a New European Welfare Regime|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MJdWwGKl2iAC&pg=PA29|year=2006|publisher=LIT Verlag M\u00fcnster|isbn=978-3-8258-9699-7|pages=29\u2013}}</ref>\n* '''{{flag|Spain}}''': [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]]<ref name=\"Egido2005\">{{cite book|author=Inmaculada Egido|title=Transforming Education: The Spanish Experience |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WY4ibawhCfoC&pg=PA14|year=2005|publisher=Nova Publishers|isbn=978-1-59454-208-4|page=14}}</ref><ref name=\"Reinares2014\">{{cite book|author=Fernando Reinares|chapter=The 2004 Madrid Train Bombings|editor1=Bruce Hoffman|editor2=Fernando Reinares|title=The Evolution of the Global Terrorist Threat: From 9/11 to Osama bin Laden's Death|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4cLQBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA32|year=2014|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=978-0-231-53743-8|page=32}}</ref>,\n* '''{{flag|Sri Lanka}}''': [[United National Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Sweden}}''': [[Moderate Party]]<ref name=\"Jakobsen2006\">{{cite book|author=Peter Viggo Jakobsen |title=Nordic Approaches to Peace Operations: A New Model in the Making?|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YcYNhfJvn08C&pg=PA184|year=2006|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-38360-8|pages=184\u2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Halilovich2013\">{{cite book|author=Hariz Halilovich|title=Places of Pain: Forced Displacement, Popular Memory and Trans-local Identities in Bosnian War-torn Communities|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6VlFAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA208|year=2013|publisher=Berghahn Books|isbn=978-0-85745-777-6|page=208}}</ref>\n* '''{{flag|Switzerland}}''': [[Conservative Democratic Party of Switzerland]]\n* '''{{flag|Taiwan}}''': [[Kuomintang]], [[People First Party (Taiwan)|People First Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Turkey}}''': [[\u0130yi Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Ukraine}}''': [[European Solidarity]], [[All-Ukrainian Union \"Fatherland\"]]\n* '''{{flag|United Kingdom}}''': [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]] \n* '''{{flag|United States}}''': [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]\n* '''{{flag|Uruguay}}''': [[National Party (Uruguay)|National Party]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Former parties===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* '''{{flag|Bolivia}}''': [[Popular Consensus]]\n* '''{{flag|Canada}}''': [[Progressive Conservative Party of Canada]]\n* '''{{flag|Chile}}''': [[National Party (Chile, 1966\u201394)|National Party